# Backend Stage 2 project

# Introduction
- This is a RESTful API purely written in Django. It is robust for CRUD as it is meant to be.
## Prerequisite
- It would be nice to have
    1. VSCode (Code Editor) __required__
    2. Python installed locally __required__
    4. REST Cleint (VSCode extension) or
    5. Basic CURL knowledge
    6. Internet connection

### Getting started
-To start the API on your local machine, make sure your'e in the root directory, run the following commands
1. pip install -r requirements.txt
2. python manage.py runserver
3. URL will be generated.

__STAY IN THE ROOT__

### Testing

- `Using REST Client`
- Select `test.rest`
- This file contain some test you can run manually.

- `Using CURL`
- Open Command Prompt
1. Create new Person
    > `curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/api -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "{\"name\" : \" New Person\" }"`
2. Get Person
    > `curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/8`
3. Update person
    > `curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/8 -X PATCH -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "{\"name\" : \" New Person -update\" }"`
4. Delete Person
    > `curl -X DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/8`



